Document: AudioStreamPlayback
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamplayback.rst
Summary: Base class for audio stream playback objects.

AudioStreamPlayback is the base class for audio stream playback objects. It defines the interface that audio streams must implement to be played back by Godot.

Inherits: RefCounted < Object

Methods:
  _mix_audio(buffer, rate, frames) → void
    Mixes audio into the buffer. This method is called by the audio server when it needs more audio data. The buffer is a Float64Array of size frames * channels. The rate is the audio server's sample rate. The frames is the number of frames to mix.

  _get_stream_name() → StringName
    Returns the name of the stream.

  _get_length() → float
    Returns the length of the stream in seconds.

  _get_loop_count() → int
    Returns the number of times the stream should loop.

  _set_loop_count(count: int) → void
    Sets the number of times the stream should loop.

  _get_loop_begin_time() → float
    Returns the time in seconds where the loop should begin.

  _set_loop_begin_time(time: float) → void
    Sets the time in seconds where the loop should begin.

  _get_loop_end_time() → float
    Returns the time in seconds where the loop should end.

  _set_loop_end_time(time: float) → void
    Sets the time in seconds where the loop should end.

  _is_playing() → bool
    Returns true if the stream is currently playing.

  _is_paused() → bool
    Returns true if the stream is currently paused.

  _get_playback_position() → float
    Returns the current playback position in seconds.

  _seek(to_pos: float, from_end: bool = false) → void
    Seeks to the specified position in seconds. If from_end is true, the position is relative to the end of the stream.

  _stop() → void
    Stops the playback.

  _mix_finished() → void
    Called when the stream finishes playing.

  _get_buffer_length() → float
    Returns the buffer length in seconds.

  _get_buffer_pos() → float
    Returns the current buffer position in seconds.

